Juventus captain Giorgio Chiellini has finally tested negative for COVID, putting him in contention for the upcoming match against Roma. The 37-year-old Italian defender tested positive for the virus on New Year’s Day and so he missed out on yesterday’s tough 1-1 draw against Napoli. Itching to return to the pitch, he’s now focused on the match against the Giallorossi on Sunday. As announced in an official statement earlier today, Chiellini has tested negative in his most recent COVID test, allowing him to return to Juventus’ squad training session tomorrow at the JTC. Nasarawa Earmarks 2.23bn For Rural  Electrification Emir Of Borgu Inaugurates Committee On Gani Durbar Festival The 37-year-old Chiellini, who is contracted to the Bianconeri until 2023, has made 11 appearances across all competitions so far this season, for a total of 777 minutes. In that time, he has performed well defensively, with the team’s main issues this campaign being up front. Juventus sit 5th in the Serie A table, three points ahead of Roma and three points behind Atalanta, who have a game in hand.